<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">hello) <p>

You do not gain all attributes of the class when you use your illusions, therefor you never get the hide skill unless your character has it to start with.  I believe that you use an illusion you gain one, if any of the attributes.  So for DE you get ultravision, for air elemental you get levitate, for water you get water breath, for earth you get a strength buff, for fire you get a damage shield, and so on.... however not all illusions necessarily give you any added benefit other than the ability to buy and sell to nearly any vendor in Norrath (to be able to visit any city providing you have the illusion) and to be able to do any quests associated specifically with that race..... it is important, however, to be cautious when using illusions.... I was recently in Cabilis giving bone chips to Guard Mozo, when out of the blue a strange NPC with a pet attacked and killed me within seconds.  After scrolling up on my chat screen after dying, I read the message:  "Enchanters such as you deserve to die" or something to that effect.... <p>

Tannera Bloodmyst, 34 enchantress, of &lt;Divine Hammer&gt;, Tarew Marr<br>
"I learn from experience... or not at all"<br>
"Wise is he who admits that he knows not all, foolish is he who believes that he does" -Plato</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
